javafxapplication1

Class Customer

  • java.lang.Object
    • javafxapplication1.Account
      • javafxapplication1.Customer

  • public class Customer
extends Account
    Overview: Customer refers to a type of bank account for a customer. Customer has a username, password, balance, level, and stringLevel. Customer is responsible for all the actions (deposit, withdrawal, purchase, check balance), and values (username, password, level, balance) stored in the text files. It is a mutable class as the values of its variables such as balance, level can be changed after being created. AF(c) = c.username + c.password + c.stringLevel + c.balance RI(c) = true when c.username != null and c.password != null
